contentrichtext.text: '''Enos''' or '''Enosh''', ([[Hebrew language|Hebrew]]: '''אֱנוֹשׁ''', <small>[[Hebrew language#Modern Hebrew|Standard]]</small> ''{{unicode|Enoš}}'', <small>[[Tiberian vocalization|Tiberian]]</small> ''{{unicode|ʼĔnôš}}''; "mortal man; sick") may refer to: ==People in religious scripture== * [[Enos (Bible)]], a genealogical figure in the Bible. * The [[Book of Enos]], one of the books that make up The Book of Mormon ** [[Enos (Book of Mormon)]], author of the Book of Enos ==People== ===First name=== * [[Enos Cabell]], a baseball player * [[Enos D.
